<title>Conversación numérica: Un grupo más</title>

<statement>
  <p>Encuentra mentalmente el valor de cada expresión.</p>
  <p><m>5 \times 2</m></p>
  <p><m>6 \times 2</m></p>
  <p><m>5 \times 6</m></p>
  <p><m>6 \times 6</m></p>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>10: I counted by 2. I just knew 5 times 2 is 10.</li>
      <li>12: I knew that 5 groups of 2 is 10, so one more group of 2 would be 12. I knew 2 times 6 is 12, and that 6 times 2 is 12 because the factors were just in a different order. I just knew it.</li>
      <li>30: I counted by 10. I just knew 5 times 6 is 30.</li>
      <li>36: I knew that 5 groups of 6 is 30, so one more group of 6 would make 36.</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>

